{
  "stem": "8784.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The, the detail of that moment on how we entered the ghetto is very sketchy in my mind.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But, but whatever I, I remember was that we knew somebody that would help us walk through the gate.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We needed to walk through a gate which was actually guarded by a German.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They, they, they were German guards already.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But if I recall, there was a Jewish [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That is, the Jewish policemen were still active and still had-- and played a role.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And one of those would lead us into the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was not a very easy-- it was a risky situation at that time because we were supposed to follow the order and enter the ghetto earlier on.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But somehow the family thought that they could stay out of the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The ghetto was an extremely [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] crowded quarters.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were people all over.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were people in buildings.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were people outside of buildings, people milling around, people not knowing what to do.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The rumor mills, the talks, the conversations [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] that at times, as a group of people, we didn't even notice that, that we were in deep trouble.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We simply thrived on the idea that we are, we no longer faced the anti-Semites on the outside, and we were amongst Jews.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And, and a life began to flourish inside the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In other words, there were people repairing shoes, and there were people listening to music, and they were almost a, a-- some semblance of normal life took on, took hold.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And, and for a while, everybody was satisfied to be there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "This was not the worst of places to be, but--",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There, there were schools.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
